    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-11-06T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-11-06T05:00:00-05:00" n="659"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d659">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.6363/134: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-11-06T19:00:00+09:00"
                            >November 6, 1934—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 6—9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>244. Department’s 184, October 31, 7 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>The foreign oil companies have today received letters from the Ministry of
                        Commerce and Industry requiring them to submit their import and storage
                        plans by November 15th. The letters conclude with a statement of which the
                        following is a translation: <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“In case you fail to respond to our request promptly, a smooth
                                execution of your company’s business plan for 1935 might be
                                interfered with.”</p>
                        </quote>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The foreign oil interests regard this as an ultimatum supported by a
                        threat. Consultations are in progress and the foreign oil companies <pb
                            facs="0845" n="755" xml:id="pg_755"/> will telegraph their
                        recommendations to their head offices within a day or two.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
